  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Remove Margins and Bottom Border Radius from Embedded Gallery Item Images\n\nModify the styling of images within embedded-gallery-item components to eliminate margins and adjust border-radius properties.\n\nRequirements:\n- Remove all margins (top, right, bottom, left) from img elements inside embedded-gallery-item\n- Remove border-radius from bottom-left and bottom-right corners of these images\n- Preserve border-radius on top corners if currently applied\n- Ensure changes apply consistently across all instances of embedded-gallery-item\n- Verify the layout remains intact after margin removal\n- Test that images align properly with their container edges\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Multiple images within a single embedded-gallery-item\n- Responsive behavior at different viewport sizes\n- Images with varying aspect ratios\n- Interaction with parent container padding/spacing",
  "title": "Remove embedded gallery image margins and bottom border-radius",
